  "commit_message": "Don't run tests via a manifest-only \"booter\" jar.\n\nWhen Surefire uses such a jar, it subsequently manually modifies the `java.class.path` system property (which by default would contain only the booter jar) to list all the jars from the `Class-Path` value in that jar's manifest. This probably isn't necessary for well-behaved Java code (including our `ClassPath`), and it causes trouble because Surefire includes a trailing empty string: `.../javax.annotation-api-1.3.2.jar:`. A trailing empty strin",
